  ],

  "data_flow_summary": [
    "1. Config: DATAVERSE_CONFIG[name] defines Radym target + sampling params",
    "2. DepthWarpDataset.__init__: merges config from DATAVERSE_CONFIG + kwargs",
    "3. DepthWarpDataset.build_dataset(): instantiates InfiniteCommonDataset(**config)",
    "4. InfiniteCommonDataset.__init__: calls _instantiate_from_config(dataset_cfg) -> Radym instance",
    "5. Radym.__init__: scans root_path/**/*.mp4 under 'rgb/' dirs, builds mp4_file_paths list",
    "6. MyDataLoader.__init__: calls DepthWarpDataset.build_dataset() -> passes InfiniteCommonDataset to DataLoader",
    "7. InfiniteCommonDataset.__getitem__(idx): reads RGB+pose+intrinsics+depth via Radym._read_data(), applies transforms, loads T5 pkl",
    "8. IterativeGEN3CDataLoader: holds N MyDataLoaders; __iter__ picks one randomly by ratio each step"
  ],

  "important_notes": [
    "InfiniteCommonDataset is NOT a torch.utils.data.Dataset subclass but acts like one (__len__ + __getitem__); MyDataLoader wraps it via DataLoader.",
    "IterativeGEN3CDataLoader is NOT a torch DataLoader; it wraps multiple MyDataLoaders and yields batches via custom __iter__.",
    "Radym is a low-level reader (not a Dataset), meant to be wrapped by InfiniteCommonDataset.",
    "T5 embeddings are loaded per-sample from .pkl files keyed by __key__ (video stem); missing embeddings trigger random retry.",
    "Megatron DP parallelism splits dataset index range across data parallel ranks in InfiniteCommonDataset.",
    "plucker_embed_corrupter.py and forward_warp_utils_pytorch.py contain only free functions (no classes)."
  ]
}
